        "text": "The gerousia presented motions before the apella. The apella then voted on the motions. However, unlike the ecclesia ([[Ecclesia (ancient Athens)]]) in [[Athens]], the apella did not debate; it merely approved or disapproved of measures. Moreover, the gerousia always had the power to veto the decision of the apella."
